; 01/07/2026.
; 
; Combination of:
;     https://github.com/behai-nguyen/linuxcnc/blob/main/building_gcodes/01_start_dremel_grinder.ngc
;     https://github.com/behai-nguyen/linuxcnc/blob/main/building_gcodes/02_draw_square.ngc
; 
; Basically, move from home to origin, start the spindle, which is a 
; Dremel grinder, then draw a square of 50 machine unit on the X-Y plane.
; 
; The X-axis motor, the Y-axis motors, and the Dremel grinder are all running
; while the square is being drawn.
; 
; When finishes drawing the square, stop the spindle, and stop the program.
; 
; Referenced Posts: 
; 
; 1. Raspberry Pi 4B LinuxCNC: Wiring the Mesa 7I96S Card and a Contactor to Control a Grinder/Router via the LinuxCNC Application
;     https://behainguyen.wordpress.com/2025/07/01/raspberry-pi-4b-linuxcnc-wiring-the-mesa-7i96s-card-and-a-contactor-to-control-a-grinder-router-via-the-linuxcnc-application/
;     https://behai-nguyen.github.io/2025/06/30/linuxcnc-06-mesa-7i96s-contactor-load.html
; 
; 2. Raspberry Pi 4B LinuxCNC: Mesa 7I96S Ethernet Motion Control, Expanded to Four CL57T Drivers and Four Nema 23 Closed-Loop Stepper Motors
;     https://behainguyen.wordpress.com/2026/06/29/raspberry-pi-4b-linuxcnc-mesa-7i96s-ethernet-motion-control-expanded-to-four-cl57t-drivers-and-four-nema-23-closed-loop-stepper-motors/
;     https://behai-nguyen.github.io/2026/06/29/linuxcnc-08-four-drivers-motors.html

(--- Setup and Safety Codes ---)
G21          (Set units to Millimeters)
G90          (Set to Absolute Distance Mode)
G17          (Select the X-Y plane)
G40          (Cancel tool radius compensation)
G49          (Cancel tool length offset)

(--- Starting the Test Square ---)
(Ensure we start at the origin at a controlled feedrate)
G0 X0 Y0 Z0   (Rapid move to the origin)
G1 F300       (Set linear interpolation movement speed to 300 mm/min)

M3 S1000      (Enable spindle)
( Gemini optimisation )
G4 P3         (Wait 3 seconds for spindle to reach full speed)

(1. Move from origin to X 50)
G1 X50 Y0

(2. From X 50, Y 0, move to Y 50)
G1 X50 Y50

(3. From X 50, Y 50, move back to X 0, Y 50)
G1 X0 Y50

(4. From X 0, Y 50, move back to X 0, Y 0)
G1 X0 Y0

M5            (Stop spindle)

(--- Program End ---)
M2           (End of program)